<h2 class="cds-h2">Consistent offline backup</h2>
<p class="cds-muted">The vault shards and the search index are only guaranteed consistent while the node is not writing, so a backup stops the node for the copy and starts it again (maintenance mode, OPS-03). Everything durable — identity, settings, hashed API keys, crawl profiles, documents, postings — lives in the data directory this archives; volatile queues are deliberately excluded, and secrets are stored hashed, never in plaintext. Run one of these on the host, from the repository or package root:</p>
<h3 class="cds-h3">Docker deployment</h3>
<pre class="cds-code">{{.DockerBackup}}</pre>
<h3 class="cds-h3">systemd deployment</h3>
<pre class="cds-code">{{.SystemdBackup}}</pre>
<h2 class="cds-h2">Restore</h2>
<p class="cds-muted">A restore wipes the data directory first — mixing shard trees from two moments corrupts both — and requires the node stopped; the script stops and restarts it. On start the node runs its shard integrity checks and heals index orphans, which doubles as the restore verification: watch the log after starting.</p>
<h3 class="cds-h3">Docker deployment</h3>
<pre class="cds-code">{{.DockerRestore}}</pre>
<h3 class="cds-h3">systemd deployment</h3>
<pre class="cds-code">{{.SystemdRestore}}</pre>
<p class="cds-muted">The full procedure and cross-version compatibility notes live in <code>doc/backup-restore.md</code>.</p>
{{end}}
{{end}}
